nt through a window well.  What a mess!  I was out of town when it happened. Water service company turned off water at meter but it had been leaking for days.  I got 4 quotes for either repair or replacement. Kenny and Sam responded quickly and excavated the site and found the crack where the copper pipe entered the foundation.  They did a spot repair with PEX pipe and replaced the shut-off valve inside the house. After seeing how corroded the copper pipe was, I decided to have the 30 ft copper line replaced with PEX.  They explained  the pros and cons and were good guys, not high pressure sales types.  Very credible. The next day they came back and replaced the copper main line from the house to the meter.  They tunneled under my front sidewalk and didn't have to cut the concrete.  They were careful to have the gas pipe mapped and avoid digging it its line.  Very efficient.  Total 5-star experience - very professional; know what they're doing; responsive; and very competitive price.  Highly recommend.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1p7YE7EYlL5-meNU2Ytfn0fW6OHX-dClH_v3LdaNxr7iaxOXBQjpin5t2yKVA_JMto6txshLVwJHMsNy59sFYvphbgNarZbxm7XouM9HKroRAZTZL-6YToquOfpFN68IaI6E7_42OHJN-V=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Fp5qCywrjrZM9AsyTJlGXzuaX51pgGD3AVbmOa8x4IP-nRe80XET3kcb64fQr53fy7uVZjqQ-FCnMl46g_djcgAMMTuAeavrAMLnO4zeD0zgPj8e1sd03P9BoLGb9ja6LPOCJtmYWskk=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2lQWNHs_HSgUH85YhtYac29lgJfpJ5vYAYbTJEFndyrUJ-S6_VggEZZfWtFQP0OoPae1vufSA62QGXe-RCWZYz6-a6B0TUshuj8s1DpISxx61Y0diaoxtacjGLU5XF_VYfPp8sLc0lqIM=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0kEkDwBOhBBqwWd707MEn3nQfdywQyZdxWu3OiXIXKNfc4dItG880cU1nOyAtQjlCT23TXHS7YXs7jcLWo-vcugCBUYftJhBSWyk8GaJHRuIFHzxUs-tmq2X7S8zdVx2Wyozj4CNuW3nM=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-29"},{"Name":"Anna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITAyxwLMgZ4MYvoQbmX5eqnFYbclP2ClNyCQpabpZ4HZ5ctw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"HIGHLY RECOMMEND Newline Pipe Solutions. Sam and Kenny did an amazing job, and it truly shows that they take pride in their work. This is an honest, professional, and ethical local business that genuinely values quality workmanship and customer trust. Their pricing is quite fair and transparent, which is refreshing to see, and the level of care and professionalism they bring to each job is outstanding. If you’re looking to support a small local business that stands behind their work and delivers excellent results, Newline Pipe Solutions is absolutely the business to support. I highly recommend them for any piping and plumbing work throughout the surrounding areas","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rich Rye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3vUtIKxV7AWQJZHYrgtwTe27yEeasHORgXumZE5_ovNyfQzS8tA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We feel lucky we found New Line and the great people there. From the 1st call they were professional, on-time polite and knowledgeable about the problems we described.\nThey arrived on time for their appointment and they were able to diagnose our problem which was a water line going to our water Heater, which also was showing signs of trouble and we found it was actually several years passed the replacement date. They had the waterline repaired in no time and the hot water Heater replaced the next day. The pricing was reasonable service was great, and thwy cleaned up after themselves Nicely. It's nice to have a good experience with service performed at your home, we do recommend them to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marcus Zimmerman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm_jmVtqidWLKjNLco5O1NS8xFDYePCFOaZdCutzCa7wDoVZM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve worked with Sam for several years on numerous remodel projects as a General Contractor, and his team consistently delivers outstanding results. Their communication is always clear and timely, and Sam’s extensive experience in the trade truly shows in the quality of their work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Greg Mathison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxWQOjTojxftvhjedyYMvrAyl26wZ556EFv_wbFS3V7x-oJpS3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been working with Sam for many years now, on many different projects (we are a builder). I have the highest level of trust with Sam, Kenny and crew to take professional and respectful care of our clients homes. Plans are always preformed to exact spec. which is especially important when dealing with complex or highly detailed builds. Their work is clean and efficient. Communication is top notch. You cant go wrong with Newline Pipe Solutions!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JESUS GRANDEZ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLeMKysyS3xFGJhTsGaR0ldXioRMkVstc1PkD3xp589J6_rqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Newline pipe solutions came out for my leaky gas water heater and Sam came out and gave me a few option to either replace the tank or go with an in demand tankless water heater.\n\nWe went with the tankless installation which we are beyond happy with, we never run out of hot water and in our utility closet he clean up a lot of space for storage.\n\nWe found a plumber for life, thank you so much for your guys help!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0xKiLyDNP8ct58PxLamI-3gXEqBFx8QyAKHzFJZRIVvFSFrBHL5sEUX4qIWYw3nkxZPSHme6Xn-tjOJU0QtGk5VmBMCFFWiXrxcZ0KPHdfOSf22J1J8hJ7q7maLpoOriDOPk1n=k-no"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Jody Brewster","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIeT2lpmqKYTeGxcy_roPwp-OH-BBY54Zdwev_OaAv4ZPe7IA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently had a leak in a shower that the first plumber we called made worse so that there was actually water dripping onto the ceiling behind the drywall below. It was a mess when we came home and recognized the water damage and knew it had to be from that. We gave Sam and Kenny a call and they came by to check it out, said they could help, were quick and fair with their estimate and got right to work. They did an outstanding job every step of the way. They were responsive, professional and clearly very experienced. They explained what had happened and what needed to be done to fix it. They gave us a reasonable and accurate estimate, and finished the work in 2 days. We are very pleased with their work and would recommend them highly to anyone needing plumbing work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Phillips","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYRxSZC81IX8DdeMwYM2WbgaRrUDMfpYBT5LnR0SWNKpH_g4Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have ony great things to say. My water main sprung a leak. Newline Pipe Solutions, responded quickly, and listened to my concerns. The gave me the best estimate, when compaired to others. They came out on the day and time they promised, took photos of the work they were doing, explained the work they had done, and even sent met photos of the project once it had been completed. Great people to work with.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
