,"Rating":5,"Description":"I had a pipe leak in my kitchen and reached out to Sean at Sammamish Pipeworks. He responded right away and was at my home quickly. Sean diagnosed the issue immediately and got it fixed fast and efficiently. He was professional, courteous, and clearly experienced. The rate was very reasonable, especially for the quality and speed of the work. I really appreciated how straightforward and stress-free the whole experience was. I’ll definitely be calling Sean again for any future plumbing needs and wouldn’t hesitate to recommend Sammamish Pipeworks to anyone looking for reliable, honest service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"elizabeth aurelio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLzit2hx5Ix2pekYw3Nh_qByTgFMgCklSOe6zNgHGYFyPFi4w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Outstanding.  Professional.  On time and respectful.  Knowledgeable.  If you want a trustworthy company with an owner that knows the business inside and out, then you want to call Sean Stanton first.  He will be the only person you’ll hire for all your plumbing needs.  If I could give more than 5 stars I surely would.  Put Sammamish Pipeworks at the top of your list.  You’ll be very happy you did.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rich Leeper","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIAM8ezbEQeaZ-FZndr0LO7RLiXVsVgOXRe3lVlz5PPt4RdHK0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a leaky hose bibb that was really old and had been painted over multiple times, making it impossible to find any markings or model numbers. The options were either to source a matching part for repair or open up a wall to replace the entire thing — something I really wanted to avoid.\n\nSean from Sammamish Pipeworks was great. He took detailed photos, did the research, and managed to track down the exact parts needed. The repair was quick, professional, and best of all — my wall stayed intact.\n\nI’m extremely happy with the service and will de