y house to check the heater and said it is not their heater problem. It is the thermostat issue. Then he said you need to change the thermometer. I asked how much it is. He said 360 plus the installation 100+ after tax it will be 500+. I remember I got my old one it’s around 35 from Home Depot. He said that the one they have is the good one high tech one. I told them that my parent is old and they don’t need those new high tech one. I denied that. After I denied this new high tech thermostat. He is not happy.\n\nHe is starting to charge me these:\n1. Diagnosed issue around $100. (The heater was installed by them and under warranty. If it is not working of course looking for them first, right? Also, the lady on the phone didn’t say anything about if there is no warranty issue they will charge me these diagnose issue payments. What if they say diagnose is going to be about $1000 or $10000 dollars. Do I still pay for it? I called them and their manager took care of this for me.)\n2. The tech didn’t ask and replaced the filter for us. ( I paid for this no problem, he did the job and replaced it. But if you can tell me the price first or ask us first would it be better? Again, you did it and tell me later) this spend $65\n3.see the picture down below. He took the old thermostat out and charged me $126. I mean 1 minute stuff and saying wiring. Come on! Everyone can see how easy it is. ( again he did the job what can I said)\n\nWhat I believe is that company is a good company but technician may have issue. Maybe they pay by job.\n\nI choose home comfort cuz Costco. Costco service always being good. I bought everything in Costco and all did good service and good installation. Home comfort When they install my unit was very professional and nice. After this happened, I have to really think about this company. Maybe it is some employees or policies they really need do something.\n\nAfter that I went to south west heater plumbing company take care my heater issue. They did it.