nt=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=9.337402\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"102494309024484923777","name":"SUNDANCE Energy (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102494309024484923777"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"10228 Main St","city":"Bothell","postal_code":"98011","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Heat pump water heater installation recognized by the US Dept. of Energy","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Installation service","enabled":true},{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"candy troy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkNhNZXaHEwPL_HOoZcMfXmvaQr7JkncZs-KITiVmfYFN_Xg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bryan is wonderful!  He has helped me so much with my fireplace multiple times. He is so knowledgable and skilled and a big help with all my Sundance systems. Initially, he came to service my old stove and discovered it needed replacement.  While he was here he helped me to choose the right replacement which has been a wonderful part of my home.  So glad I chose Sundance for my heating system replacement and grateful that I can call on Bryan for service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"orna edgar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINimlOcq57JcDBVko4-cVLMzU3ZemBOIG_c3ju5u7y5UNzYw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bryan got my fireplace insert up and running after years of dormancy.  He was professional, personable and knowledgeable about the product even though it was 13 years old.  He graciously provided instruction about use and maintenance.  Great service at a fair price.  Phone contact with the office was also great.  Thank you, Bryan and Sundance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Karen H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL96oj2VFfkSBWtfX31HNFl8iAlqSuvWwTrl_mPeKr9dkwjbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bryan serviced our gas fireplace and furnace.  He was very efficient and knowledgeable and welcomed any questions or concerns I had. Not only are both appliances nice and clean, I now have peace of mind that everything is working as it should for the winter months.  I would not hesitate in referring Sundance and will be using them again in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dmitriy Etingov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRxopaaKTnvE2jzDTbhDHnFP3C0oX7zfn23xlpSjAgFnG_TmcB=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"While the company initially appeared professional and conveniently local, and their staff were friendly and polite in communication, our experience with the technical service was disappointing. The main fireplace work was completed in the summer, but by fall, the gas fireplace stopped functioning properly. A technician was dispatched under warranty — which I appreciate, as they provide a one-year warranty — yet after two visits, the issue only worsened. Communication, punctuality, and the speed of responses are also good sides of this company.\n\nAlthough the technician was courteous and professional, his diagnosis proved incorrect. Independent testing and measurements (without any interference with the equipment) showed the problem was unrelated to the “turbulence” he claimed. I provided all my findings and data to him directly, after which the company decided to refund all charges except for the diagnostic fee — despite that diagnosis being wrong. Each service visit was delayed 1–2 weeks due to their workload both in summer and fall.\n\nThe day after the company confirmed the refund and the end of service, another vendor visited on the same day. Without telling him, he verified my conclusions and fixed the issue within an hour by replacing a small pilot orifice — a part included in the original repair order but incorrectly installed for a different gas configuration. The repair was completed twice as fast and at half the cost. Prolongated tests afterwards proved the correctness of the second vendor's work.\n\nIn summary, while the company’s staff are pleasant and responsive, the technician’s unwillingness to acknowledge diagnostic errors led to unnecessary delays, unwillingness to listen and work with clients, and costs. Persistence in the wrong direction is the enemy of accurate diagnostics and a successful business.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carl Candis Burroughs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIvFt_5c1GpDEF_KMsjoB-PefcHLDvQGvgbPk36RVJnE0lfIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am glad to write a review for Sundance and should've done this years ago.  My first hvac problem was with a gas fireplace.  Three other repair companies, yes THREE, had worked on it.  We paid a few hundred dollars to each company, and each worked on it and said it was fixed.  After a a few hours or days, each time it stopped working again.  Each time I called the company back.  Two times the company came back, said it was fixed again, but it stopped working again.  After those two return visits, I called back again, but was ghosted.  The third company did not come back at all after I called and left message that it stopped working.\nI was unhappy about all this as we love a fireplace.\nI saw a Sundance truck at a neighbor's house, talked to them, and when they came out, they finally fixed it!!  It was more complicated than the other companies could sort out.  The fix cost $800, but it was quite involved, we loved our fireplace, and it was worth it.\nYesterday Bryan of Sund,ance came out for a gas fireplace breakdown at a different house, and did a fantastic job.  We have moved to south King Co, and I'm trying to network and build relationships with contractors close to home, but for HVAC, I'm going to keep calling up to Bothell for Sundance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sheelah Doherty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVHaUKr37vtybWJZEoVxyvAPkcv17fbdmJSuV9PDPBLbtlLg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bryan Hoeck came by this morning to repair my gas fireplace. He answered all the questions I came up with. I ask A LOT of question. He fixed my fireplace and left the area cleaner than when he arrived. He also contacted me before  hand with his ETA. He was right on time. I will be using Sundance from here on out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ev Ruffcorn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLO4HGZlRjgpiQnFjdnSi6nn9OqnAG2qtuFaQULqYMzWrShdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jordan Hansen the technician was wonderful.  He completed our annual furnace checkup and was respectful of our house and equipment.  He went about his business efficiently while keeping us informed of his progress,  I would highly recommend Sundance Energy for our HVAC needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eva Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOAfhq-lyQbMrug4_7VzKVEvNRq728XwbocARwvKxnC9lsd0-SYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is my 5 year work with Sundance for regular maintenance , but I never got a chance to review . they offer great experienced staff and trustworthy team. They are on time and clean things up no need to ask . Whenever there is repair the price is fair and reasonable you won’t need to negotiate or quote other suppliers. Will continue to use them .","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
