tlUbgG3zTHPAZVKmf_kB6jDyGXtBzfJLOdfQdk7RYkFk_ETUGXxZ3jECAYYr1Ze80UFU_u9mr8DhZir3eKMzu9G9_FNKexdf88Kc3rMQfmFhJViZiqWCXTnoVsdjq0=w224-h298-k-no-pi-10-ya192.52559-ro-0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"110234765136554352922","name":"Bellevue Plumbing (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110234765136554352922"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Bridle Trails","street":"14111 NE 24th St Ste F","city":"Bellevue","postal_code":"98007","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Delivery","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Service guarantee","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Brandon Perry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInU9oHDHxl4SYXrcfUCIFaslemtMqBOaNdMxqazwMjKm3T2Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a clogged drain that turned into a flooded bathroom. Called a local plumber and they arrived within a couple hours. They cleared the blockage and found a pipe crack that they fixed on the spot. They worked clean and didn’t leave a mess behind. Cost a bit more than I hoped but worth it for the fast response. Friendly and explained everything in a way I could understand. Plumbing problems stress me out but this was handled well. Felt good to have it done fast and right. I’d call them again if I had any more pipe trouble.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lindsay Ward","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCn6etWwU7nnJnIRYUfD5kkakiO4Bz7ph4HbbJzu-3nUrjJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The technicians from this location were courteous, prompt, and made sure that their work was exceptionally well done. My main technician was Ian and his apprentice and they were able to replace my water tank, toilet, and repair my bathroom sink in under 3 hours and under $5,000. I've had good experiences with Beacon Plumbing in the past and this call helped to reinforce my expectations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pritam Bhat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeeays2XBRl-2jMd0w5ptrmuhcPctqDc9EcYRErR-dKXT0zuaN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"2 years back during winter 22 when burst pipe happened due to freezing weather, entire garage port was opened and you guys fixed the broken pipe area. Given your expertise in this area and being in the industry for so many years ,I expected that you had easily realized that this can happen again as the way the pipe runs as is it comes down and goes up to outside wall.\nAs the pipe comes up and down , water is going to stagnate again and will burst during freezing weather. Not sure the tenure of the technician and supervisor you sent was enough expert to easily figure out that.\nDue to this, the pipe bust happened again early this year at the same spot. This year I had to spend $500 to take out the new wooden planks installed last year and I have to spend another $400 to put them back.\nOn top of it to fix the pipe, the job you have done above was a 15 mins job where you charged me $600. To fix the root cause you suggested adding another value in the garage to drain this water which will cost $700 extra.\n\nI expect that you think long term from a custom point of view and provide the best service but both times it feel like you just wanted to do a patch job.\n\nI am really not happy with the service and hopeful that it does not happen to other customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marla Bennett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkZ51XrVJZio4l76bnVRa_xUaADAKz_gjwlNrXtpvxnNP5IA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Awesome service! Ryan was wonderful, explaining what was going on and what our options were. However, Stan in the office misled me on the price of the replacement toilet. We are selling the house so I asked if it would be cheaper for us to pick up a toilet ourselves. He said no, the toilets they provide are typically cheaper. When Ryan came back with the new toilet, it was over $800!! Unfortunately, due to the timing of the sale prep, we were forced to use it. I was expecting something inexpensive like what you would get at Home Depot (less than $250), and we were hit with something over three times that cost. I had been provided a verbal bid of about $700+ for the entire job. I had never been given an update before Ryan showed up at our house.\nPoor Ryan was the brunt of my disappointment, though he was still great and as helpful as he was the first visit. I will still use Bellevue Plumbing in the future, but will make sure that I get things in writing and not just trust what I am told by someone in sales.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mel Christen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYjEHulf27jnivd0JYE9iUQPRot-AOi1CJIhmp_mEuh3pi0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a plumbing emergency at my business and I called around and found that Bellevue Plumbing was the most responsive. The fixed my emergency within the hour and didn’t charge an exorbitant amount in my hour of need. I also had them work on a small job on my house and it was done so neatly and with care. My neighbors have used them and I always hear from them how great they treat their customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kendvp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5IsLSGVCyDdC_ldU-q-mrNi9I41FPXsfV8-cgrMMgkjILj4jn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I was over charged on an invoice from a previous job. So I was told by two of them over the phone that they would take it off my next invoice, I said o.k fine. Sure enough, when I get the invoice, that charge was not removed. When I called to ask why, I was told they would not take the over charge off my invoice because when I was over charged they were in the process of changing ownership, so it was not their responsibility. My thought was, it's not my responsibility either, if you change ownership in a company, you take responsibility for whatever they leave behind. Granted the over charge was only about $50.00, I don't see why I had to pay that money for nothing because of their negligence.\n\nAs far as the work goes, the plumber himself was fine, he was knowledgeable and did good work. However, the administrative staff at Bellevue Plumbing is horrible. They pulled the plumber off my job about half way through to work on another job. No warning, no notice that he was not even there. So I show up on my job wondering why it's taken four days to screw a fiberglass shower to a wall, and is still not done. My employee informed me the plumber hadn't been there for days. As a result, a lot of money was lost because of the delay.\n\nI wasn't going to write this bad review if they had taken that over charge off my invoice. But since they purposely lie to me over the phone for their own financial gain and my financial loss, I felt I should warn other contractors or home owners who are thinking of using their services.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dion Zwirner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyQzqb1bS4aB_6i3SjThL2S9xUdUp5eWrjfwutX_bUmhn76w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I hired them to remove an old water filter. Two people came when I was expecting only one - just a friend with the plumber I think.  He removed the filter which was a pretty simple job and took out a hot water dispenser.  Left a mess under the sink and then charged me over $400. for this.\nI ordered a brushed ss soap dispenser and air gap cover and twice it came in the wrong finish.  I asked for my money back and as of today I have not received it.  Called several times and each time they stall me - I have just placed it in dispute with my bank.\nI would never do business with this company and the companies they represent should think twice - terrible service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Wagner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMge0u8Jhvy623qu6eBWdj-VAWMjNxxV4_50iWsYHcbWY2xaBd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Dealing with Bellevue Plumbing has been a nightmare. A new water heater was installed incorrectly in my 72-old mother’s home, in the sense that the temperature controls were not accessible (a door from the closet where the water heater was installed has to be removed to set the temperature). A simple rotation of the heater would fix this.  A plumber came to inspect, but said the rotation was not under warranty; he removed the closet door reset the temperature to what he thought was good, and then told my mom to not change the temperature again. This is ridiculous and unprofessional – my entire life we’ve regularly raised the water temperature in winter, and lowered it in summer to save costs. I disputed the no warranty coverage since Bellevue Plumbing installed the water heater – it’s not our fault that they installed it incorrectly. After calling the office, explaining the situation, I was told that the rotation would indeed be covered under warranty. A couple days later the same plumber calls and says it’s no longer under warranty, and that the person I talked to in the office was wrong. I’m not sure if it’s plumber laziness, poor communication in their office, a dysfunctional business, or just plain greed, but I think it’s criminal that they won’t reorient their poor installation so that my senior mother can regulate her water’s temperature. Avoid this company at all costs.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
