,"ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6ELWJrGA0Bf7JnWEhUR7-tBS3BXbys-Mkj8--XT2_vpwkGmss=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"BUYER BEWARE — DO NOT HIRE HARTS!\n\nI called this company just to get a quote for an EV charger install, and it turned into a nightmare. Within 10 minutes of arriving, their technician damaged my breaker panel and wiring. He unnecessarily reached into a junction box, grabbed wires, and straightened them out — something that had nothing to do with providing a quote. In the process, he caused a hard fault on a 240V circuit that tripped both the 30A breaker and my 200A main breaker for the entire house. Sparks, smoke, and all.\n\nInstead of owning up, the technician told me “everything was fine” without even testing anything. When I complained, they sent a service manager who also claimed there was no problem — but I later discovered they had scraped away burned material and wiped paint around the breaker box to cover it up. That’s two lies and an attempted cover-up.\n\nSquare D (the manufacturer of my panel and breakers) states that breakers should be replaced after a hard fault like this. At a minimum, my 30A breaker and neighboring 20A breakers should have been replaced. The service manager reluctantly swapped out only the single 30A breaker after I argued with him, but refused to do more.\n\nMy house is only 7 years old, and now the integrity of my 200A service panel is compromised. The replacement cost runs in the thousands, yet Harts’ idea of “making it right” was to send back the same technician who caused the damage and offer me a $400 “discount” — still charging me $900 for the charger install. I declined. Another local electrician in Poulsbo quoted me $700 for the same job and did the work professionally, passing inspection.\n\nTo make matters worse, two weeks later my refrigerator (on the breaker next to the damaged one) failed — very likely related to this incident.\n\nThis company is overpriced, reckless, and dishonest. Avoid them at all costs.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1jq04GDCz-7hThEmYoGuG7bpZR1OyR8Q0oPjAXwKOqRt13n6x2OdTRZfgbwCeJkndjZSjJFvmhzpiBoX3WQIlz8LMFc3YTDDdLMrF7z-ze94_oP4-OKf1H0ugpRpnEhTTaD6x-1lH6HAw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2LairavSkqfs8aMp1HrpYijTVucCVavViouE19JAhtStjRG0eTuStqvQm_SfyG48nYxCGlML0sDki6I7lRDW73JHeZSWaAKeEf-ICt4RYV-Tfmi0wu_NGUs1vkSd14cPKuwjGYxKKujQc=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3DhjX_8R0x-zrjJiTFmyjqKHHgGusDVZy6XkEKQ7bg8R9xfPNaTlXXrvlgSnCgIJ7mu_OxAkIDfnjjqjS00vnB0Fg2jFs4M-tTrxPJ6qR6q6CiBopK6_84HYsA5c1iWqHKZSeXWFCGgcw=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2xJ-VvldziQ0bPmE_w5M4O4_zlvr78mZ4PilxZV4oqVZ2BkhfUpzwayi8pXyEiUd-e2A11NvQin69K534Nt-a5wER_MIGaQTPq3AVH4_KSHk23tAZrNSbTmn4WsonWqSL6Z0DvVnYDuEUf=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-3"},{"Name":"Jaymes Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZFiewjd10MAZtUv5piL2hXn6siFWqdFgPnykCVtNC4WcTycw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't write reviews too often but these guys are so friendly and professional. I had a EV charger installed and there was an update in permit requirements. Harts was prompt and sent their people right away to get it fixed no charge. But in both instances, they were awesome, friendly, and great to work with! Their whole operation is very efficient, I recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ed Hahne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWRsBJ2U5qx2DPoYGoZtYWVedOSETMlud5mwr8NqoC277t4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike did a great job finding the leak and coming up with a repair plan.  The house is new to us and the situation with the existing shower drain was surprising.   The plumbing repair took most of the day so the cost was probably commensurate with effort and result.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0_tb31_33F-JqXCgMGeusQNW2wjG7lXr8DkohPtr-FsGukPkJ