JELKCbp6u1XUe4TUar26kXLVhbogq3Ib2ZGUZi-4q_NBd4jFdO7dQHQYojBaCoUL47gvRTzoEIqn5Prxn7ATgpL-69cH60Knftm-iV31s=w447-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAEoVWu_8UZ3IvgEcDg0BM6CaoPrr6C6_LxkbxSiI7PtYbNQoVDOPWvsh9byBkrMtitnVEet-yGGjPBKR_Rypuo94piiYXwFI3aBPlnN0zDfFT2mrQ3tqsFO1KnMbwKVuftBgmj_=w224-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=KGsR2_XYL8S-iyrjCeepbA\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=69.09091\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.servpro.com/locations/wa/servpro-of-kirkland?utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_source=gbp","source":"servpro.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"108865727224760706879","name":"SERVPRO of Kirkland (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108865727224760706879"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Totem Lake","street":"11834 NE 112th St","city":"Kirkland","postal_code":"98033","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Gerald E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwhguSKnsCWLa2mQ3Beq9nbUKiRKFGpNKJifkR9voZTW_mfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a water leak in our building.  Rodrigo from Servpro was there within 30 mins and stayed all day finding the leak and setting up the equipment to preserve our wood floors.  He was professional, prompt, thorough and respectful of our home.  Would highly recommend this team.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrea W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTUYp1D50l8CX7looqqVu3xlL0JEs_p9vB88vD1yMm-stqa1C2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our ground floor apartment started flooding on a Saturday morning, 9/20, and it quickly became apparent that it was a pretty serious issue. After about 7 hours of the plumbers working to try to stop it, we realized we had to evacuate and called ServPro. They came out within about an hour and started pulling everything from the closest affected rooms. They worked so quickly and they were so kind. By 10:30pm, all the important stuff was packed up or moved as far from the flooding as possible. Unfortunately they had to go back TWO more days. Monday they helped pack out the rest of the apartment WHILE the restoration team was working and the whole place reeked. Tuesday, as they were moving the last of the big items onto the truck in the morning, the flooding started up again, but they still came out after hours to make a 1.5 hour drive to drop off our stuff at a storage unit and the place we’re staying so we could have our essentials. They then had to drive back to us again Wednesday to deliver the last of our items. They never slowed down, they were always kind and polite and funny, and they made a truly terrible experience a little less bad.\n\nI cannot begin to say how impressed I am with their service, their attitude, and their commitment to try to make things right.\n\nI want to call out the following people by name. They deserve a commendation, some kind of certificate of excellence, and a raise:\n\n- Scott Holeman, the project manager, a literal hero, a life saver\n- Nick D and Nick A, the dream team who worked into the night to keep our stuff from being ruined by sewer water\n- Maureen and Oriana, who didn’t let industrial machinery and active flooding slow them down and got our loose items safely packed away\n- Cale Stasiak and Keith Gorman, who made a loooong drive just to make sure we got our last few worldly possessions safely delivered (and who offered help if we needed it later on)\n\nThank you, sincerely, for helping us. It meant the world. We will never forget it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael “Michael” Jobe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRpaFtzbZT8-IpZYKE4YfriJ289KZkU28Vk_QshTEymizw8Dkm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a major mold and leak issue. Production manager Maureen Lopez and her team Were there the next day for testing and the day after for removal. The work was done in a very timely manner and Maureen kept us in the loop every step of the way. She also works with her team which was great to see. Thank you to Derick,Maureen and their team for very professional work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Davina Duerr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK7pZqF03B80NWK-GD1YNYNJ4VyliIYRXs5S0BfSdmYQTjwmw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Maureen and her team, are amazing. They were kind, caring and with all of my belonging. Seeing all of my belongings packed with such care definitely lowered my stress level.\n\nKeith and Cale who were my projects managers were exceptionally customer focused, patient and responsive to all my concerns. They both made sure that I was satisfied with the end product. My home looks better than ever.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elizabeth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFeMUJM-fC-W0MmHW9JZgKxLd7WEICMmBSNnA3OGz4GIwEfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot thank Nick Mercy enough for the care and professionalism he showed when responding to my apartment emergency. A severe upstairs toilet overflow had soaked through the flooring into the unit below, and the situation was overwhelming. From the moment he arrived, he was prompt, patient, and incredibly thorough.\nHe immediately worked to reduce further destruction and guided me through every step of the process in a way that was clear, direct, and polite. What impressed me most was his calm and steady communication—not just with me, but also with my landlord and the other parties involved. Even when my insurance company delayed and complicated the process, he kept the focus on solutions while demonstrating outstanding ethics and professionalism.\nThis was not a quick job; it took many days of cleanup, reconstruction, and careful coordination, yet he never rushed the work and consistently communicated what would happen next. The level of respect, diligence, and integrity he brought to this stressful time truly changed the outcome of the situation for the better. Because of his efforts, my landlord and I were able to move forward positively, and I am continuing my lease with confidence. I am deeply appreciative and highly recommend him.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jim Hughes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuNhK7iuXQgSclKVh_ycoLctMHwNca1YCxRsS6lMAkUNyrdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A previous contractor did a bad job on fixing a leaking shower bench that leaked again after only 3 years.  Based on the great reviews, I then contacted Servpro of Kirkland and they sent Scott and crew out to evaluate the drying process.  They were considerate and knowledgeable and avoided tearing up the ceiling below for the drying process.  Keith then handled the organization of reconstructing job.   He showed me and explained to me about why the previous work failed and gave me a couple of options of how he would handle a proper fix.  Eventually Keith brought Marco over and they both agreed on the plan moving forward.   Marco did an awesome job on the tile shelf and it has a proper rim/lip this time.  He also fixed the slope of the shelf to force water back off the shelf into the drain.   My custom glass shower was put back in with no problems and sealed better than it was the first time.   From one call to Servpro, all this work happened, in order, without me handling any contractors separately which is exactly what I wanted.  They would text me with a time and show up promptly on time.   Based on the quality of the work, they are handling the repaint/repair of the kitchen ceiling below that was affected by the leak.  Everybody I dealt with seemed to be an expert at their job which is all you could ask for when dealing with home repair.   I would highly recommend them to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter Varsanyi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkn75SKvW_pV6YEehANeCVjjQePHC8cMABwIZs1sxvayyhRCuS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I’m giving Servpro three stars because their equipment did eventually dry out the room, but the experience overall was frustrating. When I called, I was told there would be an additional $100 after-hours fee, but the final charge was $400 instead — about a third of the total bill. Maybe I misheard, but if the actual fee was $400, I wish they had made that clearer — that’s a big difference, and I might have called someone else.\n\nTheir team helped with the drying but misdiagnosed the source of the leak, saying it was from the foundation when it turned out to be the roof. I also had to keep following up to get the report, which they said was delayed due to computer issues. I will definitely get someone else next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aimee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIeaHClIVJcg5sJPnwDfsVmxp-1s3gGbyLft2UFshoKaIVNiw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Working with Scott Holeman, Project Manager, from Servpro of Kirkland was an exceptional experience during a very difficult time. When my toilet overflowed and caused water damage to both my apartment and the unit below, he stepped in with professionalism, skill, and patience that made all the difference.\n\nFrom the urgent first response to the final stages of reconstruction, he communicated clearly and politely, ensuring I understood what was happening and what to expect next. He remained calm and effective throughout, even when outside challenges—such as insurance complications—made the situation more difficult. His ability to keep all parties, including my landlord, informed and reassured was invaluable in preventing further stress and frustration.\nWhat stood out most was his strong work ethic and consistent follow-through. He took the time to do the job right, making sure every detail was addressed, and never wavered in his professionalism. His efforts not only minimized damage but helped rebuild trust with my landlord at a critical time. This level of dedication is rare, and I am truly grateful for his integrity and service. I would wholeheartedly recommend him to anyone in need of restoration work.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
{"input_id":"6c886275-f64f-4b32-b148-e21a165d940d","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Aquarius+plumbing+%26+heating+LLC/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x549069d23f5e260d:0x3f9558ed36874dc0!8m2!3d47.432463!4d-121.803803!16s%2Fg%2F11g079y8pq!19sChIJDSZeP9JpkFQRwE2HNu1YlT8?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"4581665971764678080","title":"Aquarius plumbing \u0026 heating LLC","categories":["Plumber","Service establishment"],"category":"Plumber","address":"","open_hours":{},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"","phone":"(425) 988-4300","plus_code":"","review_count":49,"review_rating":5,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":0,"2":0,"3":0,"4":0,"5":49},"latitude":47.432463,"longtitude":-121.80380299999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x549069d23f5e260d:0x3f9558ed36874dc0","place_id":"ChIJDSZeP9JpkFQRwE2HNu1YlT8","images":[],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"100443464394945306714","name":"Aquarius plumbing \u0026 heating LLC (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100443464394945306714"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"","city":"","postal_code":"","state":"","country":""},"about":[{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Roger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmuuN7gP5vXIqBWO0qzMNNbmSL-L-oNdrqrRNV6OPiC8m7Bw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally a plumber I trust.  I had a leaky drain pipe in my crawlspace that had been repaired 5 years ago.  The original plumber took a look and gave me a quote that I felt was out of line.  I sent photos to Nate and we discussed both the repair and the original quote.  His assessment was logical and reasonable so I asked him to come over a couple of days later.  The cost ended up being considerably less than the original plumber and he took extra care to keep things clean and neat when he left.  As a bonus, I enjoyed his sense of humor.  Thanks Nate!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrey Kolobov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgFNAH9wkIKvzUOzWNNbqiLgJsWO8BCNPKoTNQ065CA64fwsg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nathan of Aquarius Plumbing has fixed a number of items in my house over the years, and everything he has fixed still works. What I also really appreciate about his service is that when you reach out to him with a problem, he'll often first walk you through a few checks to verify that the problem is actually there before coming over and having you pay for the visit. Today this has saved me $300-400 easily. The garbage dispenser I thought was dead came alive after I did the steps Nathan suggested. Couldn't be happier with Nathan's helpfulness and honesty.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John Beaver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3Yb4gOv1Rx52COTMup250YRSYIEATMZdnAXtoTOx_e2BvXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's hard to find reliable and knowledgeable plumbers in Seattle, and I've kept Nate's number ever since he helped me with a water heater issue last year. He's easy to talk to, fully explains what he's doing, and doesn't price gouge like many of the plumbing operations in the area. Thanks Nate!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI3HOBqPlFKA8GwHy8WWbyGB4DN1GqWJNyH8tfM2vDy6SF4vA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nate did a great job replacing our disposal and helping me understand the root cause of the problem. He explained what needed to be done to do it the right way and found high-quality, cost-effective parts to fix the problem. He is responsive, reliable and knowledgeable. I'll definitely call him if needed for other plumbing problems in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_qCJSAHDpiTFeHLYHDtKJuLKRfMk__i4zDkkBIUAAwzypuw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've used Nate for our plumbing needs for 11 years now, and wouldn't have it any other way. In a nutshell:\n\nHe's a subject matter expert. He's diagnosed and solved problems with a few words and a couple cell phone pics, and it's immediately apparent how much experience he has.\n\nHe's professional. He tells us when he's going to arrive, gives a fair price, and doesn't nickel and dime or suggest unnecessary repairs.\n\nHe's conscientious. He's thoughtful about what he might do to your wall, ceiling, etc. before starting, careful while working, and cleans up when he's finished.\n\nTruly an exemplary tradesman. A+++","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joe Iano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK8ByvWZv855aQKIY7rJKXnHUhxPD2xz-DvSgLMwV5r85n-xtr-A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nate has tackled a couple of really challenging plumbing jobs in our old properties. He does great work, is reliable, and charges fairly. He's our first choice for plumbing work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Slava Ross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuJQrZrZzE2YCnaGQHfuh_vlztPb7B7mlQIViiW7GDWruFhQdkgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a pipe leak in our house. Nate came at the time we agreed, identified the problem and solved it. Given that walls had to be open ,  Nate suggested the least intrusive solution and was right about it. The problem was solved and he charged me according to agreed hourly rate. Nate kept me informed through all findings and fixes and it was pleasure to use his services.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Uladzimir Karpeychik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjyDcwwLQ_M_tj9JBpsEsFelyNsQ4SsSeaV910m5axX8n5tA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Over 6 years of me working with Nate, I've never thought who to call if I have a problem. He has done multiple jobs in our house and everything still looks and works great. All the jobs he did had a reasonable price, overall I am very happy.\n\nOnce, when my pipes froze in winter and he couldn't come the same day, he spent good 30 minutes on the phone with me, explained how to find the place and how to defrost it. And he didn't even charge me for that.\n\nJust a great guy.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
